gomodel:SYNGO_2756  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Postsynaptic NLGN1; neuroligin 1 is a regulator of presynaptic assembly via presynaptic beta-neurexin.\n\nFig.2: \"Neuroligin Expression in HEK293 Cells Causes Accumulation of Synapsin in Axons\"\nFig.3: \"Synaptic Vesicles Undergo Turnover at Contacts Formed with Neuroligin-Transfected HEK293 Cells\"\nFig.4: \"Neuroligin-Expressing Cells Induce the Formation of Presynaptic Structures\"\nFig.7: \"Soluble β-Neurexin Reduces Granule Cell-Induced Clustering of Synapsin in Pontine Axons\". Experimental description: - Over-expressed NLGN1; neuroligin 1 is of rat species: \"Murine neuroligin-1 and -2, and neurexin-1β cDNAs were cloned from purified cerebellar granule cells by RT-PCR. Primers were designed based upon the published rat sequences.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2756" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

